# Component Rules

## Structure
- Shared components: `components/ui/` (Shadcn) and `components/shared/`
- Feature components: `features/<feature>/components/`
- Each component in its own file, named with PascalCase

## Patterns
- Prefer Server Components by default
- Use Shadcn UI primitives — don't build from scratch what Shadcn provides
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional classNames
- Forms: always React Hook Form + Zod schema
- Loading states: Skeleton components, not spinners
- Empty states: always handle explicitly
- Error states: always handle explicitly

## Forms Template

```tsx
"use client"

import { useForm } from "react-hook-form"
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod"
import { z } from "zod"
import CustomFormField, {FormFieldType} from "@/components/shared/custom-form-field";

const schema = z.object({ ... })
type FormValues = z.infer<typeof schema>
export function MyForm() {
    const form = useForm<FormValues>({ resolver: zodResolver(schema) })
    async function onSubmit(values: FormValues) { ... }
    return ( 
    <form id="form-id" onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
        <CustomFormField
            fieldType={FormFieldType....}
            id="..."
            control={form.control}
            name="..."
            placeholder="..."
            label="..."
            type="..."
            autoCapitalize="..."
            autoComplete="..."
            autoCorrect="..."
            disabled={...}
        />
    </form> 
    )
}
```

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable
- All images must have alt text
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Radix UI primitives handle ARIA by default — don't override without reason